concurrent control with "readers" and "writers".wthe problem of the mutual exclusion of severalindependent processes from simultaneous access to a "critical section" is discussed for the case wherethere are two distinct classes of processes known as "readers" and "writers."  the "readers" may sharethe section with each other, but the "writers" must have exclusive access.  two solutions are presented:one of the case where we wish minimum delay for the readers; the other for the case where we wishwriting to take place as early as possible.cacm october, courois, p. j.heymans, f.parnas, d. l..kmutual exclusion, critical section, shared access to resources.c. .ca jb february ,   : am